HEADWORD: Apple-john
<hw>Ap"ple-john`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>. <def>A kind of apple which by
keeping becomes much withered; -- called also
<altname>Johnapple</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

